1
00:01:10,429 --> 00:01:13,724
Listen, here's the thing.

2
00:01:13,807 --> 00:01:18,645
If you can't spot the sucker
in your first half hour at the table,

3
00:01:18,729 --> 00:01:20,981
then you are the sucker.

4
00:01:28,530 --> 00:01:31,909
Guys around here'll tell ya...
you play for a living.

5
00:01:31,992 --> 00:01:35,996
It's like any other job.
You don't gamble. You grind it out.

6
00:01:36,080 --> 00:01:40,334
Your goal is to win
one big bet an hour, that's it.

7
00:01:40,417 --> 00:01:43,670
Get your money in when you have the best
of it, and protect it when you don't.

8
00:01:43,754 --> 00:01:45,756
Don't give anything away.

9
00:01:45,839 --> 00:01:48,675
That's how I've paid my way
through half of law school.

10
00:01:48,717 --> 00:01:52,179
A true grinder.

11
00:01:52,262 --> 00:01:57,226
See, I learned how to win a little at
a time. But finally, I've learned this...

12
00:01:57,267 --> 00:02:01,772
If you're too careful, your
whole life can become a fuckin' grind.

13
00:02:10,072 --> 00:02:13,826
This is Teddy KGB's place.

14
00:02:13,909 --> 00:02:17,496
- Five hundred.
- You won't find it in the Yellow Pages.

15
00:02:17,579 --> 00:02:19,706
Nope.
Not tonight.

16
00:02:19,790 --> 00:02:21,750
No? What?

17
00:02:25,462 --> 00:02:27,923
Give me three stacks
of high society.

18
00:02:42,396 --> 00:02:46,191
Thirty thousand.
Count it.

19
00:02:51,822 --> 00:02:57,244
- That's good.
- So, you're sitting the apple.

20
00:02:57,286 --> 00:03:00,414
- Good. Want a cookie?
- No.

21
00:03:01,749 --> 00:03:03,667
He doesn't look like much,

22
00:03:03,751 --> 00:03:07,421
but KGB is connected all the way
to the top of the Russian mob.

23
00:03:07,504 --> 00:03:10,507
He's the one guy in the game
you don't want to fuck with.

24
00:03:10,591 --> 00:03:12,843
But if you're looking
for high stakes,

25
00:03:12,926 --> 00:03:14,887
this is the only place
in town.

26
00:03:14,970 --> 00:03:18,599
They all know me as a small-timer,
but that's about to change.

27
00:03:25,856 --> 00:03:28,358
Joey Knish
is a New York legend.

28
00:03:28,442 --> 00:03:31,236
He's been a rounder,
earning his living at cards...

29
00:03:31,320 --> 00:03:33,906
since he was 19 years old.

30
00:03:33,989 --> 00:03:36,408
What are you,
holdin' those for somebody?

31
00:03:36,492 --> 00:03:39,828
Uh, yeah,
I'm holding 'em for you.

32
00:03:39,912 --> 00:03:41,872
- You should be.

33
00:03:41,955 --> 00:03:44,750
'Cause I hope you're not thinking
of putting all that glimmer in play.

34
00:03:44,833 --> 00:03:48,128
He's as close to a friend
as there is in this place.

35
00:03:48,170 --> 00:03:51,090
- Come here.
- But tonight,
I don't want to see him.

36
00:03:51,173 --> 00:03:53,425
Now, you don't wanna
butt onions with these guys.

37
00:03:53,509 --> 00:03:56,637
'Cause they'll chew you up,
take your whole bankroll.

38
00:03:58,138 --> 00:04:00,474
- So you say.
- There's plenty of easy games.

39
00:04:00,557 --> 00:04:03,811
We get outta here, get some coffee,
ride over to that soft seat in Queens.

40
00:04:03,852 --> 00:04:06,271
I know what I'm doing.

41
00:04:08,565 --> 00:04:11,318
You're making a run at it,
aren't you?

42
00:04:11,402 --> 00:04:13,987
Rolling up a stake
and going to Vegas.

43
00:04:14,029 --> 00:04:17,533
I'm right, right?

44
00:04:17,616 --> 00:04:19,785
- I can beat the game.
- Maybe.

45
00:04:19,868 --> 00:04:22,329
Maybe this is a game
can be beat.

46
00:04:22,413 --> 00:04:25,207
But you know you can beat the 10-20
at the Chesterfield and the Hi-Low...

47
00:04:25,290 --> 00:04:27,668
at that goulash joint
on 79th Street.

48
00:04:29,253 --> 00:04:33,006
Okay.
I understand.

49
00:04:35,217 --> 00:04:38,929
I understand.
Back to battle.

50
00:04:41,807 --> 00:04:44,685
The game in question is
No-Limit Texas Hold 'Em.

51
00:04:44,726 --> 00:04:47,479
Minimum buy-in $25,000.

52
00:04:47,563 --> 00:04:50,899
A game like this doesn't come together
often outside the casinos.

53
00:04:50,983 --> 00:04:53,110
The stakes attract
rich flounders,

54
00:04:53,193 --> 00:04:55,612
and they in turn
attract the sharks.

55
00:05:00,242 --> 00:05:03,954
No-Limit Texas Hold 'Em
is the Cadillac of poker.

56
00:05:04,037 --> 00:05:07,458
Each player is dealt
two cards face down.

57
00:05:07,541 --> 00:05:10,711
Five cards are then dealt
face up across the middle.

58
00:05:10,753 --> 00:05:14,214
These are community cards everyone can
use to make the best five card hand.

59
00:05:15,799 --> 00:05:18,677
The key to the game is playing
the man, not the cards.

60
00:05:18,761 --> 00:05:21,180
Bet an eight ball.

61
00:05:23,348 --> 00:05:27,478
There's no other game in which fortunes
can change so much from hand to hand.

62
00:05:27,561 --> 00:05:30,731
A brilliant player can get
a strong hand cracked, go on tilt...

63
00:05:30,814 --> 00:05:33,776
and lose his mind along with
every single chip in front of him.

64
00:05:33,859 --> 00:05:37,988
This is why the World Series of Poker is
decided over a No-Limit Hold 'Em table.

65
00:05:38,072 --> 00:05:40,741
Some people, pros even,
won't play No-Limit.

66
00:05:40,783 --> 00:05:43,077
They can't handle
the swings.

67
00:05:44,453 --> 00:05:46,872
But there are others,
like Doyle Brunson,

68
00:05:46,955 --> 00:05:50,000
who consider No-Limit
the only pure game left.

69
00:05:52,127 --> 00:05:57,674
Like Papa Wallenda said..."Life is on
the wire. The rest is just waiting."

70
00:05:57,758 --> 00:06:00,219
Pass it to you.

71
00:06:03,222 --> 00:06:05,641
All right, I raise.

72
00:06:05,724 --> 00:06:08,560
- I'm gonna raise five hundred.
- Fold.

73
00:06:11,230 --> 00:06:14,066
It's a position raise.
I call it.

74
00:06:19,113 --> 00:06:21,365
Here's the beauty of this game.

75
00:06:23,117 --> 00:06:26,370
- Go ahead.
- I just got
top two pair on the flop,

76
00:06:26,453 --> 00:06:28,414
and I want to keep him
in the hand.

77
00:06:28,497 --> 00:06:31,875
Against your average guy,
I'd set a bear trap, hardly bet at all.

78
00:06:31,959 --> 00:06:34,920
Let him walk into it.
But KGB's too smart for that.

79
00:06:35,003 --> 00:06:37,840
So, what I've got to do
is over-bet the pot,

80
00:06:37,923 --> 00:06:40,008
make it look like
I'm trying to buy it.

81
00:06:40,092 --> 00:06:44,388
- I bet $2,000.
- Then he plays back at me,
and I get paid off.

82
00:07:15,878 --> 00:07:18,255
Call.

83
00:07:18,338 --> 00:07:21,592
My guess is Teddy's on a flush draw.

84
00:07:23,260 --> 00:07:25,262
Burn and turn.

85
00:07:27,055 --> 00:07:29,016
There's my money card, nine of hearts.

86
00:07:29,057 --> 00:07:31,101
I got a full house.

87
00:07:33,187 --> 00:07:35,522
- To the bettor.
- Check's good.

88
00:07:35,564 --> 00:07:39,359
Now I hope
a spade falls and Teddy makes his flush.

89
00:07:39,401 --> 00:07:43,447
That way he'll bet strong, and I'll beat
him with my nines full over aces.

90
00:07:48,702 --> 00:07:52,372
I'm going to bet...

91
00:07:52,414 --> 00:07:55,876
Bet...

92
00:07:55,918 --> 00:07:58,962
$15,000.

93
00:08:01,090 --> 00:08:03,550
Time.

94
00:08:06,470 --> 00:08:09,306
I want him to think
that I'm pondering a call,

95
00:08:09,389 --> 00:08:13,227
but all I'm really thinking about
is Vegas and the fucking Mirage.

96
00:08:28,283 --> 00:08:32,246
All right, your 15, plus
I have another 33 to raise you.

97
00:08:32,329 --> 00:08:34,289
Um...

98
00:08:38,460 --> 00:08:42,089
Yeah, I'm gonna go all in, 'cause
I don't think you got the spades.

99
00:08:45,426 --> 00:08:49,763
You are right.
I don't have spades.

100
00:08:54,977 --> 00:08:58,063
I know before
the cards are even turned over.

101
00:09:02,192 --> 00:09:05,279
Aces full, Mike.

102
00:09:34,683 --> 00:09:36,602
Get up.

103
00:09:39,605 --> 00:09:41,523
Come on.
Come on.

104
00:09:46,361 --> 00:09:49,490
- Want some?
- No.

105
00:09:49,531 --> 00:09:52,701
I'm down to the felt, Knish.
I lost everything.

106
00:09:52,785 --> 00:09:56,955
Man, I lost my case money.
I lost my tuition.

107
00:09:58,540 --> 00:10:02,127
It happens to everyone.
Time to time, everyone goes bust.

108
00:10:02,211 --> 00:10:05,255
You'll be back in the game
before you know it.

109
00:10:05,339 --> 00:10:08,383
I'm done.
I'm out of it.

110
00:10:08,467 --> 00:10:10,969
They all say that
at first.

111
00:10:11,053 --> 00:10:14,181
Hey, man, let me stake you.
Standard deal, you know.

112
00:10:14,264 --> 00:10:18,519
Fifty percent of your winnings.
If you lose, it's on me.

113
00:10:20,312 --> 00:10:22,523
I'd just throw it away.

114
00:10:25,567 --> 00:10:29,029
- You still got the truck?
- Sure.

115
00:10:29,113 --> 00:10:31,073
Come on.

116
00:10:45,546 --> 00:10:49,508
You don't hear much
about guys who take their shot and miss,

117
00:10:49,591 --> 00:10:51,844
but I'll tell you
what happens to 'em.

118
00:10:51,927 --> 00:10:54,763
They end up humping crappy jobs
on graveyard shifts,

119
00:10:54,847 --> 00:10:57,850
trying to figure out
how they came up short.

120
00:10:59,435 --> 00:11:01,603
See, I had this picture
in my head.

121
00:11:01,687 --> 00:11:04,690
Me sitting at the big table,
Doyle to my left,

122
00:11:04,773 --> 00:11:09,236
Amarillo Slim to my right,
playing in the World Series of Poker.

123
00:11:09,319 --> 00:11:13,657
And I let that vision
blind me at the table against KGB.

124
00:11:13,741 --> 00:11:16,577
Now, the closest I get
to Vegas is west New York,

125
00:11:16,618 --> 00:11:19,204
driving this lousy route
handed down from Knish...

126
00:11:19,288 --> 00:11:22,583
to rounders who forget
the cardinal fuckin' rule...

127
00:11:22,624 --> 00:11:24,626
Always leave yourself outs.

128
00:11:24,668 --> 00:11:27,171
- Hey, Moogie.
- Let me ask you a question.

129
00:11:27,254 --> 00:11:30,716
In a legal sense, can fuckin'
Steinbrenner just move the Yankees?

130
00:11:30,799 --> 00:11:33,427
Does he have the fuckin' right
to just move them?

131
00:11:33,510 --> 00:11:36,263
I don't know.
How should I know that?

132
00:11:36,305 --> 00:11:40,267
- You didn't learn that yet?
- No, we get to Steinbrenner
in the third year of law school.

133
00:11:40,350 --> 00:11:43,103
Oh.

134
00:11:43,187 --> 00:11:47,399
- Take care, man.
- Yeah.

135
00:11:59,328 --> 00:12:01,246
The judges' game.

136
00:12:01,330 --> 00:12:05,459
I'd heard about it for years on the
street, before I was even in law school.

137
00:12:05,501 --> 00:12:09,129
A rotating group of ten or twelve
judges, prosecutors and professors.

138
00:12:09,213 --> 00:12:11,632
They all have money,
and in my playing days...

139
00:12:11,715 --> 00:12:15,177
it would have been pretty sweet to have
any one of them owing me favors.

140
00:12:15,260 --> 00:12:17,805
Only problem is, no one
can get in the game anymore.

141
00:12:17,888 --> 00:12:21,934
One rounder, Crispy Linetta,
sat under some pretense,

142
00:12:22,017 --> 00:12:26,480
but they found out he was a pro,
he couldn't cross the street
without a legal hassle.

143
00:12:26,563 --> 00:12:29,441
Even his regular club,
Vorshay's, got shut down.

144
00:12:29,525 --> 00:12:32,444
Place had been open
since 1907.

145
00:12:32,528 --> 00:12:34,405
Oh, Michael.

146
00:12:34,488 --> 00:12:37,157
- You got some things for me?
- Yes, I do.

147
00:12:37,199 --> 00:12:39,535
Put 'em on the desk,
it's all right.

148
00:12:40,953 --> 00:12:42,913
Kid, he paying you
for this late night shit?

149
00:12:42,996 --> 00:12:46,333
Oh, well, knowledge is
my reward, sir.

150
00:12:46,417 --> 00:12:48,794
- Let me tell you, it ain't worth it.

151
00:12:48,877 --> 00:12:51,171
Why don't you become a jockey,
do something useful.

152
00:12:51,213 --> 00:12:54,007
- Kid's a little tall, isn't he, Gene?

153
00:12:54,049 --> 00:12:57,052
Enough with the Belmont
recruiting spiel. Your bet.

154
00:12:57,094 --> 00:12:59,346
- All right. I call.
- Michael is lead counsel...

155
00:12:59,430 --> 00:13:01,765
in the Moot Court
you're presiding over next week, Gene.

156
00:13:01,849 --> 00:13:03,976
Besides, he could use
the background if he's gonna...

157
00:13:04,059 --> 00:13:07,104
clerk for one of you fellas
this summer, right?

158
00:13:07,187 --> 00:13:11,275
Abe, I thought you liked the kid. Why do
you want to make him a civil servant?

159
00:13:11,358 --> 00:13:14,737
Yeah, look... a word to the wise.
Stay in the private sector.

160
00:13:14,820 --> 00:13:18,782
That Nassau defense attorney's game?
They use our chips for coasters.

161
00:13:18,866 --> 00:13:21,201
The amazing thing is, in this
collection of great legal minds,

162
00:13:21,285 --> 00:13:24,037
there isn't a single
real card player.

163
00:13:24,121 --> 00:13:27,666
- I call.
- Raise.

164
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:29,877
Um, the professor raises.

165
00:13:31,795 --> 00:13:35,174
Mike?
Michael, I would have just called.

166
00:13:35,257 --> 00:13:37,176
No, you're good.

167
00:13:37,259 --> 00:13:40,053
All right, I call.

168
00:13:40,095 --> 00:13:42,681
I don't know if I'm going to bring
my legal career to a crashing halt...

169
00:13:42,765 --> 00:13:46,935
before it even starts,
but I just can't help myself.

170
00:13:47,019 --> 00:13:48,979
- Good.
- I'm in.

171
00:13:49,062 --> 00:13:51,398
- Read 'em and weep.

172
00:13:55,152 --> 00:13:57,571
Threes check.

173
00:14:02,284 --> 00:14:05,245
Check to Martin and Lewis
over there.

174
00:14:05,329 --> 00:14:08,332
- Check to the raiser.
- Czechoslovakia.

175
00:14:08,415 --> 00:14:12,669
- What's the limit?
- $20. Big bet's $20.

176
00:14:12,753 --> 00:14:16,840
Okay. Good.
There's $20.

177
00:14:16,924 --> 00:14:21,095
You've seen half a hand. How the
fuck are you betting into us?

178
00:14:21,178 --> 00:14:23,764
You sure this is wise, Abe?
It's your money the kid's bettin' with.

179
00:14:23,847 --> 00:14:28,227
It's plenty wise.
We know what we're holding,
and we know what you're holding.

180
00:14:28,310 --> 00:14:31,021
The fuck you know what we all got.

181
00:14:31,105 --> 00:14:34,024
Summer clerkship in your office says
I know what you're holding.

182
00:14:34,108 --> 00:14:36,568
I don't bet
with jobs like that.

183
00:14:36,652 --> 00:14:40,030
Let's just say I'll put you at the top
of the list if you're right.

184
00:14:40,114 --> 00:14:44,034
Okay. Well, you
were looking for that third three,

185
00:14:44,118 --> 00:14:46,954
but you forgot that Professor Green
folded it on Fourth Street,

186
00:14:47,037 --> 00:14:49,206
and now you're representing
that you have it.

187
00:14:49,289 --> 00:14:51,708
The D.A. made his two pair,
but he knows they're no good.

188
00:14:51,792 --> 00:14:55,421
Judge Kaplan was trying to squeeze out
a diamond flush, but he came up short,

189
00:14:55,504 --> 00:14:57,881
and Mr. Eisen is futilely hoping
that his queens are gonna stand up.

190
00:14:57,965 --> 00:15:01,301
So, like I said,
the Dean's bet is $20.

191
00:15:01,343 --> 00:15:04,304
- Well, kiss my ass.
- Kiss my ass.

192
00:15:08,100 --> 00:15:11,103
- What'd you have, Abe?
- Nothin' but a busted straight.

193
00:15:11,186 --> 00:15:13,772
- Oh, come on.
- It's good enough to win. Take it down.

194
00:15:13,856 --> 00:15:17,317
All right, kid, your first assignment.
Pull up a seat next to me.

195
00:15:17,401 --> 00:15:19,987
Oh, I'd like to. I can't, I can't.
I don't play cards.

196
00:15:20,070 --> 00:15:23,657
- Get outta here!
- See you tomorrow.

197
00:15:23,741 --> 00:15:26,076
- Whose deal?
- My deal.

198
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:28,912
- I like the kid, Abe.
- Good kid.

199
00:15:28,996 --> 00:15:31,290
Smart kid.

200
00:15:31,373 --> 00:15:34,793
I tell ya, it's hard leaving that game.

201
00:15:34,877 --> 00:15:38,422
An open invitation
to lay with those lambs.

202
00:15:38,505 --> 00:15:40,424
But I'm retired.

203
00:15:42,885 --> 00:15:45,637
The truth is, I can always
find games, though.

204
00:15:45,721 --> 00:15:49,600
Easy games, tough games, straight games,
crooked games, home games.

205
00:15:49,683 --> 00:15:53,854
I can turn this truck onto the Jersey
Turnpike and be at the Taj in two hours.

206
00:15:55,272 --> 00:15:57,191
But I've made promises.

207
00:16:00,402 --> 00:16:02,821
I'm just a law student now.

208
00:16:04,573 --> 00:16:06,492
Hello?

209
00:16:06,575 --> 00:16:08,494
- Hey.
- Hey.

210
00:16:10,079 --> 00:16:12,873
- How'd it go?
- Oh, great.

211
00:16:17,127 --> 00:16:21,423
I am sick of that fucking route.

212
00:16:21,507 --> 00:16:24,426
Don't worry.
A few more semesters...

213
00:16:24,510 --> 00:16:27,554
Mmm.

214
00:16:27,638 --> 00:16:30,057
Oh, I gotta go.

215
00:16:30,140 --> 00:16:33,393
- I'm really late.
- Oh, just stay here.
I'll be really quick.

216
00:16:33,477 --> 00:16:36,105
- You won't feel a thing.

217
00:16:36,188 --> 00:16:38,524
We both know
that's not true.

218
00:16:38,607 --> 00:16:41,276
Besides, you should
get some sleep.

219
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:43,529
These fuckin' long nights
are killing me.

220
00:16:43,612 --> 00:16:45,572
They never used to.

221
00:16:45,614 --> 00:16:47,658
Yeah, well, that's different.
I mean, that was like...

222
00:16:47,741 --> 00:16:50,411
buy in at 8:00, next thing
you know it's morning.

223
00:16:50,494 --> 00:16:53,580
But hey, you know, I think
I'm hooked up for this summer.

224
00:16:53,664 --> 00:16:55,707
Hooked up how?

225
00:16:55,791 --> 00:16:59,586
Well, after I left you last night at the
library, I impressed Judge Marinacci.

226
00:16:59,628 --> 00:17:01,755
I think I might be in line
for a clerkship.

227
00:17:03,257 --> 00:17:05,968
Tell me more.

228
00:17:06,051 --> 00:17:09,096
Well, those guys were
all playing cards, and...

229
00:17:09,179 --> 00:17:11,807
Just hear me out now,
hear me out.

230
00:17:11,890 --> 00:17:14,810
They were playing cards
and I read his hand blind.

231
00:17:17,771 --> 00:17:21,191
So, instead of coming home, you went
and played cards with some judge?

232
