Hey, fuckin' Grama.
How you doin'?

668
00:43:53,742 --> 00:43:55,953
- I was just thinkin' about you.
You know, I could use you.
- Oh, yeah?

669
00:43:56,036 --> 00:43:58,497
See me in, like, two weeks.
I'll put you back on the payroll.

670
00:43:58,580 --> 00:44:03,043
Well, I got some bad news for ya, Worm.
I'm out on my own now.

671
00:44:03,085 --> 00:44:05,587
- Really?
- Yeah.

672
00:44:05,671 --> 00:44:07,756
Go figure.

673
00:44:07,840 --> 00:44:11,218
There were a lot of angry people when
you went away. A lot of people were mad.

674
00:44:11,260 --> 00:44:13,595
I know, Grama, that's why I'm trying
to put together a roll here.

675
00:44:13,679 --> 00:44:15,681
A lot of people coming up to me,
asking if I could help,

676
00:44:15,722 --> 00:44:17,724
asking if I knew
where to find you.

677
00:44:17,766 --> 00:44:20,394
- So, it got me to thinkin'.
- Really, you thinkin' now? That's big.

678
00:44:20,477 --> 00:44:23,647
Hey, Jesus! Come on!
Take it easy.

679
00:44:23,730 --> 00:44:26,150
It's just
a friend of mine.

680
00:44:26,233 --> 00:44:29,570
Hey! Easy, easy, easy, easy.
God!

681
00:44:29,653 --> 00:44:32,740
Get the fuck outta here.
What did I say?

682
00:44:32,823 --> 00:44:36,076
- Hey, man, take it easy!
- Get the fuck outta here!

683
00:44:37,661 --> 00:44:40,456
Okay.
Here's what I'm thinkin'.

684
00:44:40,539 --> 00:44:44,042
Instead of you owing 15 grand spread out
to five guys, you owe 25 to me.

685
00:44:44,126 --> 00:44:46,587
What? Where the fuck
do you get off? 25 grand?

686
00:44:46,628 --> 00:44:49,214
Where the fuck
do I get off?

687
00:44:49,256 --> 00:44:51,258
Ohh.

688
00:44:51,341 --> 00:44:55,262
Here's how it is. 25 grand,
and the juice is still runnin'.

689
00:44:55,345 --> 00:44:57,806
Jesus Christ.

690
00:44:57,890 --> 00:45:00,017
What the fuck are you doin', man?
You were my partner.

691
00:45:00,100 --> 00:45:02,019
No, no,
I was your lackey.

692
00:45:02,102 --> 00:45:04,021
But I learned
a few things, Worm.

693
00:45:04,104 --> 00:45:07,858
I consolidated
your outstanding debt.

694
00:45:07,941 --> 00:45:11,195
Where'd you get
the scratch for that?

695
00:45:11,278 --> 00:45:14,490
You've been rolling fags
in the Village again.

696
00:45:14,573 --> 00:45:16,992
- Still a wise ass. Unbelievable.

697
00:45:17,076 --> 00:45:19,620
What I did was go partners
with an old friend of yours.

698
00:45:19,703 --> 00:45:23,040
Teddy KGB backed me.

699
00:45:23,123 --> 00:45:25,584
Bullshit.
Bullshit.

700
00:45:26,668 --> 00:45:30,255
Teddy's got plenty of goons.

701
00:45:30,339 --> 00:45:32,424
Why would he put you
under his flag?

702
00:45:32,466 --> 00:45:37,221
Because as soon as he heard your name,
he became real excited for the prospect.

703
00:45:37,304 --> 00:45:39,932
What, so you bought me up, Grama?

704
00:45:39,973 --> 00:45:43,268
Yeah, got a real sweet deal, too.
30 cents on the dollar.

705
00:45:43,310 --> 00:45:46,438
There's not a lot of faith in you
out there in the business community.

706
00:45:46,522 --> 00:45:49,399
Great, so you're a banker now, Grama.
That's really classy.

707
00:45:49,483 --> 00:45:53,320
Not exactly. I don't have to tell you
my collection methods.

708
00:45:53,404 --> 00:45:55,322
Oh, God. All right, look.

709
00:45:55,406 --> 00:45:57,366
Just take it easy,
all right?

710
00:45:57,449 --> 00:45:59,493
I'll scrape something together,
and I'll find you this week.

711
00:45:59,576 --> 00:46:01,870
- That's just what I figured.
- No, no, no.

712
00:46:01,954 --> 00:46:05,833
- So I'm gonna take what you
got on you right now.
- Here. Fine.

713
00:46:05,874 --> 00:46:09,461
Have yourself
a ball, okay?

714
00:46:11,505 --> 00:46:14,049
God!

715
00:46:14,133 --> 00:46:16,844
Damn!

716
00:46:29,106 --> 00:46:31,024
Excuse me.

717
00:46:42,619 --> 00:46:44,538
Mind if I sit?

718
00:46:44,621 --> 00:46:47,040
Michael.

719
00:46:47,124 --> 00:46:50,043
Please, please.
Sit, sit.

720
00:46:52,212 --> 00:46:54,673
That was a nifty trick
the other night.

721
00:46:56,717 --> 00:46:58,844
- It was wonderful.
- Thank you.

722
00:46:58,886 --> 00:47:02,639
Marinacci and the D.A. were ready to cut
cards for your services at that point.

723
00:47:05,225 --> 00:47:09,021
Of course,
it was an altogether different trick,
that disappearing act...

724
00:47:09,062 --> 00:47:11,064
you pulled today
at your group's meeting.

725
00:47:11,148 --> 00:47:15,861
- Yeah. Well, I figure
I owe you an explanation.
- Ah, not to me.

726
00:47:15,903 --> 00:47:18,030
I'm sure there's
a good reason you left.

727
00:47:18,072 --> 00:47:20,407
You'll just have to
work harder. Prepare.

728
00:47:20,449 --> 00:47:23,911
- And smooth things out with the others.

729
00:47:23,952 --> 00:47:27,247
Right. Yeah.
Okay.

730
00:47:27,289 --> 00:47:30,959
- Okay, well, thanks.
- Stay. Take a drink.

731
00:47:32,419 --> 00:47:34,338
- Jamie?
- Yeah?

732
00:47:34,421 --> 00:47:37,049
- Another glass, darling.
- Sure.

733
00:47:37,091 --> 00:47:39,218
- What are you drinking?
- Gin. Always gin.

734
00:47:39,301 --> 00:47:41,261
- Here you go.
- Thanks, dear.

735
00:47:41,303 --> 00:47:43,680
Thank you.

736
00:47:43,764 --> 00:47:47,101
I know a magician doesn't
divulge his secrets, but...

737
00:47:47,142 --> 00:47:49,812
I'm no magician.

738
00:47:49,895 --> 00:47:53,273
Well, if it wasn't magic,

739
00:47:53,357 --> 00:47:55,943
how did you know
what everyone held?

740
00:47:56,026 --> 00:47:58,946
It's a combination
of things.

741
00:47:59,029 --> 00:48:01,073
Um, I was watching
when the cards came out.

742
00:48:01,156 --> 00:48:05,619
That's... That's just an old habit
with me, like breathing.

743
00:48:05,702 --> 00:48:07,746
You watch the cards.

744
00:48:07,788 --> 00:48:11,250
I watch the cards also, but I watch
the players reacting to the cards.

745
00:48:11,291 --> 00:48:13,877
That's how I knew the D.A.
made his two pair,

746
00:48:13,961 --> 00:48:16,380
and Judge Kaplan
missed the flush.

747
00:48:16,463 --> 00:48:18,799
I was watching their eyes
when they checked their river cards.

748
00:48:18,882 --> 00:48:22,136
- Their faces tell you everything.
- You watch the man.

749
00:48:22,219 --> 00:48:26,390
l... I never knew you had
to calculate so much at cards.

750
00:48:32,062 --> 00:48:35,816
All right, here's the thing.
You only play premium hands.

751
00:48:35,899 --> 00:48:38,694
You only start
with jacks or better split,

752
00:48:38,777 --> 00:48:41,280
nines or better wired,
three high cards to a flush.

753
00:48:41,363 --> 00:48:44,199
If it's good enough to call, you gotta
be in there raising, all right?

754
00:48:44,283 --> 00:48:48,162
I mean, tight, but aggressive.
And I do mean aggressive.
That's your style, Professor.

755
00:48:48,245 --> 00:48:50,998
I mean, you gotta...
you gotta think of it as a war.

756
00:48:51,081 --> 00:48:55,127
You are officially never
invited to our game again.

757
00:48:57,296 --> 00:49:01,091
I don't blame you. Put a guy
like me in a game like that,
the cards don't even matter.

758
00:49:01,175 --> 00:49:03,093
I'll play it blind.

759
00:49:05,012 --> 00:49:08,348
Michael,

760
00:49:08,432 --> 00:49:11,518
- May I tell you a story?
- Please.

761
00:49:11,602 --> 00:49:16,899
For generations,
men of my family have been rabbis.

762
00:49:16,982 --> 00:49:20,027
In Israel,
before that in Europe.

763
00:49:20,110 --> 00:49:23,822
It was to be my calling.
I was quite a prodigy.

764
00:49:23,864 --> 00:49:26,283
The pride of my yeshiva.

765
00:49:26,366 --> 00:49:28,577
The elders said I had
a 40-year-old's understanding...

766
00:49:28,660 --> 00:49:32,331
of the midrash
by the time I was 12.

767
00:49:32,372 --> 00:49:34,666
But by the time
I was 13,

768
00:49:36,168 --> 00:49:38,504
I knew I could never
be a rabbi.

769
00:49:38,545 --> 00:49:40,506
Why not?

770
00:49:40,547 --> 00:49:43,884
Because for all
I understood of the Talmud,

771
00:49:45,886 --> 00:49:48,555
I never saw
God there.

772
00:49:48,639 --> 00:49:51,391
- You couldn't lie to yourself.
- I tried.

773
00:49:51,475 --> 00:49:53,393
Tried like crazy.

774
00:49:53,477 --> 00:49:56,730
I mean, people were
counting on me.

775
00:49:56,772 --> 00:49:59,858
But yours is
a respectable profession.

776
00:49:59,942 --> 00:50:01,902
Not to my family.

777
00:50:01,944 --> 00:50:06,323
My parents were destroyed,
devastated by my decision.

778
00:50:08,158 --> 00:50:13,455
My father sent me away
to New York...

779
00:50:13,539 --> 00:50:16,291
to live
with distant cousins.

780
00:50:16,375 --> 00:50:19,169
Eventually, l...
I found my place,

781
00:50:19,253 --> 00:50:22,005
my life's work.

782
00:50:23,424 --> 00:50:25,843
What then?

783
00:50:25,926 --> 00:50:28,846
I immersed myself fully,
I studied the minutiae,

784
00:50:28,929 --> 00:50:31,348
I learned everything I could
about the law.

785
00:50:31,432 --> 00:50:34,393
I mean, I felt deeply inside
that it was what I was born to do.

786
00:50:37,646 --> 00:50:41,024
- And did your parents get over it?
- No.

787
00:50:41,108 --> 00:50:45,237
I always hoped
that I would find...

788
00:50:45,279 --> 00:50:48,240
some way to change
their minds, but...

789
00:50:51,952 --> 00:50:53,871
They were
inconsolable.

790
00:50:55,873 --> 00:50:58,917
My father never spoke
to me again.

791
00:51:02,921 --> 00:51:06,258
If you had to do it
all over again,

792
00:51:06,300 --> 00:51:10,137
would you make
the same choices?

793
00:51:10,179 --> 00:51:12,473
What choice?

794
00:51:15,976 --> 00:51:19,146
The last thing I took away
from the yeshiva is this...

795
00:51:21,398 --> 00:51:23,817
We can't run
from who we are.

796
00:51:26,070 --> 00:51:28,322
Our destiny chooses us.

797
00:51:31,658 --> 00:51:34,286
Hey.
L'chayim.

798
00:51:55,140 --> 00:51:57,059
Hey.

799
00:51:57,142 --> 00:51:59,103
Hey, where you been?
I've been freezing my ass off.

800
00:51:59,186 --> 00:52:02,773
- What happened?
- Ah, ran into a door.
Don't worry about it.

801
00:52:02,856 --> 00:52:05,943
- What happened?
- Hey! She crossed her legs
too fast, all right?

802
00:52:06,026 --> 00:52:08,153
- Just mind your own business.
- You comin' up?

803
00:52:08,195 --> 00:52:10,531
No, I've been standing out here
all this time just to say hi.

804
00:52:10,572 --> 00:52:13,200
Listen, things haven't
been that smooth on the home front,

805
00:52:13,283 --> 00:52:15,869
so tone it down
a little, all right?

806
00:52:15,953 --> 00:52:18,580
- Tone down what, motherfucker?
- Great.

807
00:52:18,664 --> 00:52:21,166
- Never mind.

808
00:52:23,585 --> 00:52:26,547
When you become a big shot lawyer,
could you find us an elevator building?

809
00:52:26,588 --> 00:52:28,549
Shut up.

810
00:52:32,469 --> 00:52:35,305
What, did you
get robbed?

811
00:52:35,389 --> 00:52:38,058
Um, not exactly.

812
00:52:39,184 --> 00:52:42,980
Wait, wait, wait.
Did she split on you?

813
00:52:43,063 --> 00:52:46,108
Oh, God.

814
00:52:47,818 --> 00:52:51,864
Oh, my God. Mike, she made off
with your sheets.

815
00:52:51,905 --> 00:52:54,408
I always told her she'd be
a good card player.

816
00:52:54,491 --> 00:52:57,828
- Know exactly when
to release a shitty hand.
- Come on, Mike, forget that.

817
00:52:57,911 --> 00:53:00,706
This girl is obviously
wrapped way too tight for living.

818
00:53:00,748 --> 00:53:04,835
No, she was a good... I knew it.
I fuckin' knew it.

819
00:53:09,923 --> 00:53:11,925
It's depressing.

820
00:53:11,967 --> 00:53:14,052
You can't trust 'em.
You can't trust 'em at all.

821
00:53:14,136 --> 00:53:17,931
I mean, look at you.
You domesticated yourself for this girl.

822
00:53:17,973 --> 00:53:20,768
You took yourself out of the life.
You walked the fuckin' line for her.

823
00:53:20,851 --> 00:53:24,229
And the minute you want a little
of it back, she walks out on you.

824
00:53:24,271 --> 00:53:27,232
It's just like
the saying says, you know?

825
00:53:27,274 --> 00:53:32,237
In the poker game of life,
women are the rake.

826
00:53:32,279 --> 00:53:35,616
- They are the fuckin' rake.
- What the fuck are you talking about?

827
00:53:35,657 --> 00:53:39,119
What saying?

828
00:53:39,203 --> 00:53:43,707
I don't know.
But there oughta be one.

829
00:53:46,627 --> 00:53:51,465
- You know what cheers me up
when I'm feelin' shitty?
- What?

830
00:53:51,507 --> 00:53:54,093
Rolled up aces over kings.

831
00:53:57,513 --> 00:53:59,473
- That right?
- Yeah.

832
00:53:59,515 --> 00:54:03,852
Check raising stupid tourists
and taking huge pots off 'em.

833
00:54:03,936 --> 00:54:08,440
- Yeah?
- Stacks and towers of checks
I can't even see over.

834
00:54:08,482 --> 00:54:12,986
Playin' all night,
high-limit Hold' Em at the Taj.

835
00:54:13,070 --> 00:54:16,657
- Where the sand turns to gold.
- Fuck it, let's go.

836
00:54:18,158 --> 00:54:20,744
- Don't tease me.
- Let's play some fuckin' cards.

837
00:54:34,675 --> 00:54:36,635
The poker room at the Mirage in Vegas...

838
00:54:36,677 --> 00:54:39,513
is the center of
the poker universe.

839
00:54:39,555 --> 00:54:41,849
Doyle Brunson, Johnny Chan,
Phil Helmuth...

840
00:54:41,932 --> 00:54:44,184
The legends consider it
their office.

841
00:54:44,268 --> 00:54:46,186
Every couple of days
a new millionaire shows up...

842
00:54:46,270 --> 00:54:48,439
wanting to beat
a world champion.

843
00:54:48,522 --> 00:54:51,692
Usually they go home
with nothing but a story.

844
00:54:51,734 --> 00:54:53,819
Down here, the millionaires are scarce
or they're playing craps,

845
00:54:53,861 --> 00:54:56,363
but there's still
plenty of money for the taking.

846
00:54:56,447 --> 00:54:58,365
In fact, on the weekends
you can't get a game in the city,

847
00:54:58,449 --> 00:55:01,660
because all the New York rounders
are taking care of the tourists here.

848
00:55:01,702 --> 00:55:05,289
Hey, hey, why don't you warm up
a seat for me. I'll catch up with you.

849
00:55:05,372 --> 00:55:07,708
- What?
- Look.

850
00:55:07,791 --> 00:55:10,627
- I got certain needs
I gotta attend to, okay?
- Hey, good.

851
00:55:10,711 --> 00:55:13,046
- I mean, I'm overdue.
- Good, man, hey, I was startin'
to wonder about you.

852
00:55:13,088 --> 00:55:16,925
I thought, maybe, you know,
the boys upstate brought about
a few changes in you.

853
00:55:17,009 --> 00:55:20,846
Hey, in your dreams,
lover.

854
00:55:28,395 --> 00:55:30,397
- Hey, Mikey!
- Hey.
- Hey, Mike.

855
00:55:30,481 --> 00:55:34,026
This is beautiful.
Welcome to the Chesterfield south.

856
00:55:34,109 --> 00:55:36,403
- Ho!
- Changing $500.

857
00:55:36,445 --> 00:55:39,281
Come all the way to Atlantic City
just to see your mugs, huh?

858
00:55:39,364 --> 00:55:41,408
Twice in one week.

859
00:55:41,492 --> 00:55:44,495
For someone who don't play, you spend
a lot of time in card rooms.

860
00:55:44,578 --> 00:55:46,497
This is what
I like to see, huh?

861
00:55:46,580 --> 00:55:49,666
Mike McDermott where he belongs...
sittin' with the scumbags.

862
00:55:49,750 --> 00:55:52,377
Tellin' jokes,
draggin' the occasional pot.

863
00:55:52,419 --> 00:55:56,381
Occasional? Yeah, like my ex-wife
occasionally went out with other men.

864
00:55:56,465 --> 00:56:00,928
Forget her, Face. I was actually gonna
try and make some real money tonight.

865
00:56:01,011 --> 00:56:04,640
But in honor of Mike's
alley-like return to the ring,

866
00:56:04,723 --> 00:56:06,683
I'll sit with you all
for a while.

867
00:56:06,767 --> 00:56:08,811
Hey, don't do us
any favors, Knish.

868
00:56:08,894 --> 00:56:12,189
- They're about to go to
the board to fill these seats.
- Bet it.

869
00:56:12,272 --> 00:56:15,776
I raise. You know, if we wanted
to take each other's rolls,

870
00:56:15,859 --> 00:56:17,778
we could have just
stayed home.

871
00:56:19,446 --> 00:56:21,407
These two have no idea...

872
00:56:21,448 --> 00:56:24,910
what they're about to
walk into.

873
00:56:24,952 --> 00:56:26,954
Down here to have a good time,
they figure...

874
00:56:26,995 --> 00:56:30,374
why not give poker a try?

875
00:56:30,457 --> 00:56:32,543
After all, how different
can it be from the home games...

876
00:56:32,626 --> 00:56:34,586
they've played
their whole lives?

877
00:56:36,672 --> 00:56:41,135
All the luck in the world isn't
gonna change things for these guys.

878
00:56:41,218 --> 00:56:44,471
They're simply overmatched.

879
00:56:46,723 --> 00:56:50,602
We're not playing together,
but then again, we're not playing
against each other either.

880
00:56:50,644 --> 00:56:54,898
It's like the Nature Channel. You don't
see piranhas eating each other, do you?

881
00:57:02,740 --> 00:57:05,951
They wear their tells
like signs around their necks.

882
00:57:05,993 --> 00:57:08,996
Facial tics, nervous fingers.

883
00:57:09,079 --> 00:57:10,998
A hand over a mouth.

884
00:57:11,081 --> 00:57:14,001
The way a cigarette
is smoked.

885
00:57:14,042 --> 00:57:17,171
Little unconscious gestures
that reveal the cards in their hands.

886
00:57:17,254 --> 00:57:19,673
We catch everything.

887
00:57:19,715 --> 00:57:22,301
If a fish acts strong,
he's bluffing.

888
00:57:22,384 --> 00:57:25,846
If he acts meek,
he's got a hand. It's that simple.

889
00:57:31,852 --> 00:57:34,313
- How are you, you workaholics?
- Worm.

890
00:57:34,396 --> 00:57:36,982
Good to see ya.
Glad you're out.

891
00:57:37,024 --> 00:57:39,151
Number's changed,
of course.

892
00:57:39,193 --> 00:57:41,320
Lotta games this weekend,
so you're gonna need the number.

893
00:57:41,403 --> 00:57:43,363
- I'll give you a ring.
- Hey, Worm?

894
00:57:43,405 --> 00:57:45,699
Do they allow people like you
in places like this?

895
00:57:45,741 --> 00:57:49,328
Zagosh, when you get yourself a job,
